==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Honeybee
<hw>Hon"ey*bee`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any bee of the genus <gen>Apis</gen>, which lives in communities
and collects honey, esp. the common domesticated hive bee (<spn>Apis
mellifica</spn>), the Italian bee (<spn>Apis ligustica</spn>), and the
Arabian bee (<spn>Apis fasciata</spn>). The two latter are by many
entomologists considered only varieties of the common hive bee. Each
swarm of bees consists of a large number of workers (barren females),
with, ordinarily, one queen or fertile female, but in the swarming
season several young queens, and a number of males or drones, are
produced.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Honeyberry</ent>⟦br⟧
